    {
        "content": "<p>I believe this file is what you're looking for: <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/FixedPointApproximants.html\">https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/FixedPointApproximants.html</a><br>\nMore specifically, <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/FixedPointApproximants.html#OrdinalApprox.lfpApprox\">lfpApprox</a> defines the transfinite iteration sequence for a bundled monotone <code>f : α →o α</code>, and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/SetTheory/Ordinal/FixedPointApproximants.html#OrdinalApprox.lfp_mem_range_lfpApprox\">lfp_mem_range_lfpApprox</a> says that it achieves a fixed point at some ordinal stage.</p>",
        "id": 455529687,
        "sender_full_name": "Joe Watt",
        "timestamp": 1722480066
    },
